 =20
    <div>
      <h2 id=3D"cc916ed68fc8" class=3D"text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-5 p-1 bg-=
gray-100 font-raleway overflow-hidden">
       =20
          <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V=
12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#cc916ed68fc8">
            <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V12.=
0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
          </a>
       =20
        Post Processor Sections
      </h2>
      <p class=3D"mt-3">Vectric post processors are broken down into sectio=
ns to aid clarity, try to write your post processors in a similar style to =
aid debugging.</p>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"8ae400a0ff3a" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#8ae400a0ff3a">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          File Comments
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">A section where you can describe the post pr=
ocessor and record any changes to the post processor, each line is a commen=
t and starts with a =E2=80=98+=E2=80=99 character or a =E2=80=98|=E2=80=99 =
character.<code></code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ History</code></p><p c=
lass=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Who When What</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ =3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D</code></p><p c=
lass=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Tony 14/07/2006 Written</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><=
code>+ Mark 26/08/2008 Combined ATC commands, stop spindle on TC</code></p>=
<p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D</code></p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"9142fcc83f6f" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#9142fcc83f6f">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          Global File Statements
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">Statements are items that are either used on=
ly once, or have static values throughout the file. Write statement names i=
n upper case letters for clarity.</p><div class=3D"flex flex-col items-cent=
er"><span class=3D"font-bold"></span><table class=3D"w-full stripey"><tbody=
><tr><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Statement</p></th><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Result</=
p></th></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>POST_NAME=3D"Text Output Arcs(m=
m)(*.txt)</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">The name that will appear in=
 the post processor list</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>FILE_=
EXTENSION=3D"txt"</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">The file extension t=
hat the file will be given</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>UNI=
TS=3D"MM"</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">The units that the file outp=
uts (INCHES or MM)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>PRINT_DIREC=
T=3D"YES"</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">The machine tool manufacture=
r has supplied a driver (usually a printer driver) thatn can directly accep=
t the NC file output (For example see <em>Generic HPCL_Arcs.pp</em>)</p></t=
d></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>RAPID_PLUNGE_TO_STARTZ=3D"YES"</code=
></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Indicates that plunge moves to Plunge (Z2) =
height (that is set on the material setup form) are rapid moves</p></td></t=
r><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>DIRECT_OUTPUT=3D"Display Name|Manufacture=
rs.Document"</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">The control software uses=
 a document interface that can directly accept the NC file output.</p></td>=
</tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>ROTARY_WRAP_Y=3DA</code></p></td><td><=
p class=3D"mt-3">The moves in the Y axis are to be wrapped around a cylinde=
r of the specified diameter. The "Y" values will be output as "A"</p></td><=
/tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>ROTARY_WRAP_X=3DB</code></p></td><td><p=
 class=3D"mt-3">The moves in the X axis are to be wrapped around a cylinder=
 of the specified diameter. The "X" values will be output as "B"</p></td></=
tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>SPINDLE_SPEED_RANGE =3D 1 15 4500 15000<=
/code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Spindle speed for this machine is outp=
ut as a range of integer numbers between 1 and 15 representing the actual s=
peed in RPM of the spindle, (between 4500 and 15000 RPM in the quoted examp=
le). For an example, see the file: <em>Roland_MDX-40_mm.pp</em></p></td></t=
r><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>SUBSTITUTE =3D "O1 S1 O2 S2 On Sn"</code>=
</p></td><td><div><p class=3D"mt-3">This command allows you to substitute a=
 character output within the variables (such as <code>[TOOL_NAME]</code>) a=
nd substitute that character, with another. This feature can be useful for =
those cases where particular characters cause errors on an NC control.</p><=
p class=3D"mt-3">The characters are entered in pairs, Original - Subsititue=
d.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">For example MACH 3 control software uses parenthese=
s as comment delimiters, and does not allow nested comments. Most tools wit=
hin the Vectric Tool Database have parentheses within the =E2=80=9CName=E2=
=80=9D section; if these names are output, this would cause an error within=
 Mach3. The command <code>SUBSTITUTE =3D "({)} "</code> would convert the (=
) characters to {} characters, and avoid this error. For an example, see th=
e file: <em>Mach2_3_ATC_Arcs_inch.pp</em></p></div></td></tr><tr><td><p cla=
ss=3D"mt-3"><code>INVERSE_TIME_MODE=3D"YES"</code></p></td><td><div><p clas=
s=3D"mt-3">Rotary: Enables / Disables output of the feedrate F in Inverse T=
ime Feed Mode. In this mode, we're expected to complete a move in one divid=
ed by the F number of minutes.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">In GCode, this would us=
ually be a G93 to switch on Inverse Time Mode, or a G94 to set Units per Mi=
nutes mode.</p></div></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>LASER_SUPPOR=
T =3D "YES"</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Indicates that this post-p=
rocessor supports laser toolpaths (if the <a href=3D"https://docs.vectric.c=
om/docs/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/laser-module/index.html" class=3D"tex=
t-blue-500">Laser Module</a> is installed).</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=
=3D"mt-3"><code>MIN_ARC_RADIUS =3D 0.01</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3=
">Optional minimum arc radius. Arcs which have a radius smaller than this v=
alue will be replaced with a single straight line move.</p></td></tr><tr><t=
d><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>MAX_ARC_RADIUS =3D 1000.0</code></p></td><td><p c=
lass=3D"mt-3">Optional maximum arc radius. Arcs which have a radius greater=
 than this value will be polygonized.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3=
">POST_BASE</p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">This is a <strong>no longer suppo=
rted</strong> way of inheriting the content of another post-processor. See =
the <a href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/=
migrating-post-processor-post_base/index.html" class=3D"text-blue-500">POST=
_BASE Migration</a> page for more details.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></d=
iv></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"9c8450186907" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#9c8450186907">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          Tape Splitting Support
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">A section that describes how a long toolpath=
 output will be split:</p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>TAPE_SPLITTING=3DMAX_NUM_=
LINES LINE_TOL "FILENAME_FORMAT" START_INDEX INDEX_ON_FIRST_FILE</code></p>=
<p class=3D"mt-3">For example a command of:</p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>TAPE=
_SPLITTING=3D1000 100 "%s_%d.tap" 1 "YES"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3">would=
 lead to...</p><p class=3D"mt-3">Output will be split into multiple files o=
f a maximum of 1000 lines (+ however many lines in there are within the foo=
ter section of the post processor), if a retract move exists after line 900=
 (1000 =E2=80=93 100), the file will be split at that move. If the file was=
 called "toolpath" the split files would be named toolpath_1.tap, toolpath_=
2.tap etc. The first toolpath output will be "toolpath_ 1.tap" there will b=
e no file named "toolpath" without an index number, (as <code>INDEX_ON_FIRS=
T_FILE=3DYES</code> is used), unless the file was less than 1000 lines long=
, in which case the file would not be split.</p><div><div class=3D"p-2 mt-3=
 mb-3 border-l-2 bg-gray-100 border-blue-500 overflow-hidden"><p class=3D"t=
ext-lg mb-2"><strong>Note</strong></p><p class=3D"mb-3">Some controllers th=
at require NC files to be split, also have limitations on the number of cha=
racters within a filename. For example they may require the file to be name=
d with the MSDOS style 8.3 filename format. This should be considered when =
naming the output file.</p></div></div></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"02427ef2af4e" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#02427ef2af4e">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          Line Terminating Characters
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>LINE_ENDING=3D"[13][12]"</code></p><p =
class=3D"mt-3">Decimal values of the characters appended to each separate l=
ine of the post processed file. (Will usually be [13][10]) (Carriage return=
, line feed) for any controller that can read a windows or MSDOS format tex=
t file.</p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"1431bdb9dfb8" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#1431bdb9dfb8">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          Block Numbering
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">If you wish to add line numbers to the outpu=
t file, the current line number is added with the variable [N]. The behavio=
ur of this line number variable is controlled by the following variables:</=
p><div class=3D"flex flex-col items-center"><span class=3D"font-bold"></spa=
n><table class=3D"w-full stripey"><tbody><tr><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Statemen=
t</p></th><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Result</p></th></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-=
3"><code>LINE_NUMBER=3D0</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Value at whic=
h the line numbering should start</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><c=
ode>LINE_NUMBER_INCREMENT=3D10</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Increme=
ntal value between line numbers</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><cod=
e>LINE_NUMBER_MAXIMUM=3D99999</code></p></td><td><div><p class=3D"mt-3">The=
 maximum line number to output, before cycling to the <code>LINE_NUMBER_STA=
RT</code> value again.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">Important - Some controllers ha=
ve a limit to the number of lines that can be displayed on the control</p><=
/div></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
     =20
    </div>
