         =20
          Optional Format Flags
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">The output values can be further modified by=
 using the optional format flags:</p><div class=3D"flex flex-col items-cent=
er"><span class=3D"font-bold"></span><table class=3D"w-full stripey"><tbody=
><tr><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Flag</p></th><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Function</p><=
/th><th><p class=3D"mt-3">Default (without flag)</p></th></tr><tr><td><p cl=
ass=3D"mt-3"><code>-</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Left Justify the =
output</p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Values are right justified</p></td></t=
r><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Pr=
efix the value with '+' or '-'</p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Only negative =
values are prefixed</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>0</code></=
p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">If value has fewer characters than the set min=
imum, the value is prefixed with zeroes</p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Value=
s is prefixed with blanks spaces</p></td></tr><tr><td><p class=3D"mt-3"><co=
de>#</code></p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-3">Values is always output with a se=
parator character ( in practice this would only change the output value if =
the value is set to output integer values only)</p></td><td><p class=3D"mt-=
3">When output is set to integer only, separator charactor is not appended =
to value.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>
