2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          HEADER
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output at the s=
tart of the file</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-----------------------=
----------------------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin HEADER=
</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3">T=
he header is the location for the instructions that are output once, at the=
 start of the file, these generally setup modal commands for the controller=
.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">For example, the Header might contain a command to d=
isplay the filename on the controller and a series of =E2=80=9CG-Codes=E2=
=80=9D to set the machine up, for instance G20 to tell the control that the=
 moves are in inches, or G21 to tell the control that the moves are in mill=
imetres.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">Variables that you might wish to be within th=
e header section, could include:</p><p class=3D"mt-3"></p><p class=3D"mt-3"=
><strong>Information about the Material Block</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum e=
xtent in X =3D [XMIN]</li><li>Minimum extent in Y =3D [YMIN]</li><li>Minimu=
m extent in Z =3D [ZMIN]</li><li>Maximum extent in X =3D [XMAX]</li><li>Max=
imum extent in Y =3D [YMAX]</li><li>Maximum extent in Z =3D [ZMAX]</li><li>=
Length of material in X =3D [XLENGTH]"</li><li>Length of material in Y =3D =
[YLENGTH]"</li><li>Depth of material in Z =3D [ZLENGTH]"</li></ul><p class=
=3D"mt-3"><strong>Home Position Information</strong></p><ul><li>Home X =3D =
[XH]</li><li>Home Y =3D [YH]</li><li>Home Z =3D [ZH]</li><li>Rapid clearanc=
e gap or Safe Z =3D [SAFEZ]</li></ul><p class=3D"mt-3"><strong>Details of t=
he first tool to be used.</strong></p><ul><li>Tool Number =3D [T]</li><li>T=
ool name =3D [TOOLNAME]</li></ul><p class=3D"mt-3"><strong>Initial cutting =
speeds</strong></p><ul><li>Feed Rate used for cutting and plunging into the=
 material =3D [F]</li><li>Feed Rate whilst tool is Cutting the material =3D=
 [FC]</li><li>Feed Rate whilst tool is plunging into the material =3D [FP]<=
/li></ul><p class=3D"mt-3">Actual values depend on the UNITS set (see Globa=
l File Settings) Defaults are either MM/Minute or Inches/Minute, but the ou=
tput can be changed to suit by setting the appropriate =E2=80=9CVAR FEED_RA=
TE=E2=80=9D formatting.</p><p class=3D"mt-3"><strong>Spindle Speed</strong>=
</p><ul><li>Spindle Speed =3D [S] R.P.M.</li></ul></div>
