--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output for a ne=
w segment ( new toolpath with current toolnumber)</code></p><p class=3D"mt-=
3"><code>+---------------------------------------------------</code></p><p =
class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin NEW_SEGMENT</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"C=
ommands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><em>For an example of a NEW_SEGMENT se=
ction, see the file: Mach2_3_ATC_Arcs_inch.pp</em></p><p class=3D"mt-3">Com=
mands that are output when a new toolpath uses the currently selected tool,=
 but perhaps a different spindle speed is required or the machine requires =
additional instructions.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">Any commands that are used in=
 the NEW_SEGMENT section should not need to be included within the TOOLCHAN=
GE section as a tool-change will also automatically call the instructions i=
n the NEW_SEGMENT section.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">Variables that are commonly=
 used include.</p><ul><li>Spindle Speed =3D [S] R.P.M.</li><li>M3 M Code of=
ten used to turn spindle on (Clockwise rotation).</li><li>M5 M Code often u=
sed to turn spindle off.</li></ul></div>
