These might be instructions to return the tool to the home position, switch=
 the spindle off or switch the power off to the drives.</p><p class=3D"mt-3=
"><code>+---------------------------------------------------</code></p><p c=
lass=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output at the end of the file</code></p><p c=
lass=3D"mt-3"><code>+---------------------------------------------------</c=
ode></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin FOOTER</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><c=
ode>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3">Variables that are commonly used=
 include.</p><ul><li>G00 [XH] [YH] [ZH] Rapid to X,Y,Z Home position.</li><=
li>M05 M Code often used to turn spindle off.</li><li>M30 M Code often used=
 to signify the end of the file.</li></ul></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"5d37ad3acafb" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#5d37ad3acafb">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          SPINDLE_ON
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3">The Spindle On section is used after the Hea=
der and allows the Spindle on commands to be used in a combination Milling/=
Laser Post Processor.</p><p class=3D"mt-3">If Spindle on commands are used =
in the Header, this Block should not be included.</p><p class=3D"mt-3"><cod=
e>+---------------------------------------------------</code></p><p class=
=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output at the end of the file</code></p><p class=
=3D"mt-3"><code>+---------------------------------------------------</code>=
</p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin SPINDLE_ON</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><c=
ode>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3">Variables that are commonly used=
 include.</p><ul><li>M3 for Spindle On</li><li>[S] For Spindle Speed</li></=
ul></div>
     =20
    </div>
