       =20
          <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V=
12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#e33de1d4f24c">
            <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V12.=
0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
          </a>
       =20
        Other Less Frequently Used Sections
      </h2>
     =20
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"96d1d794abaa" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#96d1d794abaa">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          FEED_RATE_CHANGE
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output when fee=
d rate changes</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------=
--------------------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin FEED_RAT=
E_CHANGE</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D=
"mt-3"><em>For an example of a FEED_RATE_CHANGE section, see the file: Grav=
ograph_IS200.pp</em></p><p class=3D"mt-3">Commands that are output when the=
 feed rate is changed. This section is not often used as many controllers w=
ill accept feed rate changes appended to other instructions, but sometimes =
used with HPGL variants.</p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"37b06bbb2233" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#37b06bbb2233">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          FIRST_PLUNGE_MOVE
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output for the =
First Plunge Move, in a series of plunge moves.</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"=
><code>+---------------------------------------------------</code></p><p cl=
ass=3D"mt-3"><code>begin FIRST_PLUNGE_MOVE</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><cod=
e>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><em>For an example of a FIRST_PLUN=
GE_MOVE section, see the file: Holz-Her_7123_ATC_Arcs_mm.pp</em></p><p clas=
s=3D"mt-3">This section is often used on machines that do not fully support=
 simultaneous 3D movement, for example the Z Axis cannot travel as fast as =
the X &amp; Y Axis. Another use of this section might be to include command=
s that you wish to output whenever the first plunge move occurs. For exampl=
e, commands to switch on a plasma torch. Multiple plunges would normally on=
ly be output within a ramping move, so this command would be useful for con=
trols that automatically rapid between cuts and where instructions such as =
revised speeds and feed need to be specified on the first plunge move and t=
hese instructions are not required for subsequent plunge moves within the r=
amping operation.</p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"357a62a3a6c0" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#357a62a3a6c0">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          PLUNGE_MOVE
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output for Plun=
ge Moves</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------=
--------------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin PLUNGE_MOVE</c=
ode></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><em>=
For an example of a PLUNGE_MOVE section, see the file: Burny_arc_inch.pp</e=
m></p><p class=3D"mt-3">This section is often used on machines that do not =
fully support simultaneous 3D movement, for example the Z Axis cannot trave=
l as fast as the X &amp; Y Axis. Another use of this section might be to in=
clude commands that you wish to output whenever a plunge move occurs. For e=
xample, commands to switch on a plasma torch.</p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"75817cb2cc26" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#75817cb2cc26">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          RETRACT_MOVE
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output for Retr=
act Moves</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+------------------------------=
---------------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin RETRACT_MOVE<=
/code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><e=
m>For an example of a RETRACT _MOVE section, see the file: Burny_arc_inch.p=
p</em></p><p class=3D"mt-3">A use of this section might be to include comma=
nds to switch off a plasma torch.</p></div>
     =20
        <h3 id=3D"69ef93293f62" class=3D"text-xl font-semibold p-2 mb-2 mt-=
6 font-bold font-raleway overflow-hidden">
         =20
            <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs=
/V12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#69ef93293f62">
              <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V1=
2.0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
            </a>
         =20
          DWELL_MOVE
        </h3>
        <div><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-------------------------------------=
--------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+ Commands output for Dwel=
l Commands</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>+-----------------------------=
----------------------</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>begin DWELL_MOVE</=
code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><code>"Commands"</code></p><p class=3D"mt-3"><em=
>For an example of a DWELL_MOVE section, see the file: Mach2_3_Arcs_inch.pp=
</em></p><p class=3D"mt-3">This command was introduced for VCarve Pro 7.5 a=
nd Aspire 4.5 and later. It is used with a drilling toolpath, when a Dwell =
time has been specified in the program. If this section is not defined any =
dwell commands are ignored, but the rest of the drilling toolpath will be o=
utput as normal. The DWELL variable is documented in the Variables section.=
</p></div>
     =20
    </div>
