    <div>
      <h2 id=3D"315f6f76cf81" class=3D"text-2xl font-bold mb-3 mt-5 p-1 bg-=
gray-100 font-raleway overflow-hidden">
       =20
          <a class=3D"inline-block" href=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V=
12.0/VCarvePro/ENU/Help/form/post-processor-editing/#315f6f76cf81">
            <img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://docs.vectric.com/docs/V12.=
0/VCarvePro/shared/icons/link.svg">
          </a>
       =20
        Post Processor Naming Conventions
      </h2>
      <div><p class=3D"mt-3">Within the post processors that ship with the =
products you will see the following terms or abbreviations used:</p><ul><li=
>Arc or Arcs =3D The post processor will output true arcs within the design=
 as Arc moves, (G2,G3,Radius of Arc etc.).</li><li>Inc =3D Arcs are output =
with centre coordinates incremental to the last move.</li><li>Abs =3D Arcs =
are output with absolute coordinate values.</li><li>ATC =3D The post proces=
sor will output Automatic Tool Change (ATC) commands.</li><li>WY =3D Wrappe=
d out output post processor =E2=80=93 Y values wrapped around X axis</li><l=
i>WX =3D Wrapped out output post processor =E2=80=93 X values wrapped aroun=
d Y axis</li><li>TSnumber =3D Tape Splitting post processor.</li><li>An opt=
ional number is the maximum number of lines that will be output within a si=
ngle file. Files that exceed this number of lines will be split into multip=
le files. (See Tape Splitting Support for more details).</li><li>(mm) =3D T=
he post processor units are Metric.</li><li>(inch) =3D The post processor u=
nits are English (Imperial) inches.</li><li>(*.xyz) =3D The file extension =
that the output file will be created with.</li></ul></div>
     =20
    </div>
